      <ResourceHeader>
         <ResourceName>Possible Type II and IV Radio Bursts Observed by WIND/WAVES and STEREO/WAVES</ResourceName>
         <ReleaseDate>2026-02-17T18:14:32</ReleaseDate>
         <Description>The WIND/WAVES and STEREO/WAVES catalog provides curated data on interplanetary Type II and IV radio bursts. This catalog details slow-drift radio features (Type II) caused by shocks and long-duration, broadband emission (Type IV) associated with moving plasmoids, focusing on decameter-hectometric (DH) wavelengths.</Description>
